      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm, i\u0027m not sure. the RFC (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4254) uses the word \"message\" frequently, although that would be even less accurate here. i considered ExecCommand or ExecCmd, but i\u0027m worried it might be confusing since i also have a \"Cmd\" field.\n\nin go\u0027s http package (and many other http libraries that i\u0027ve used) take the approach of passing two objects, one representing the request and one for sending the response. if i were to do something similar here, i\u0027d probably just use a string for the request and rename this to something like ExecResponder. i think that that may be a bit harder to use than this, though.\n\ni think i\u0027ll stick with \"Req\" for now since all of the functionality is tied to the original request, but i agree that it\u0027s not perfect and i\u0027ll try some more to think of something that\u0027s more accurate.",
